==English==

===Noun===
'''milling'''

#The notchs around the edge of a [[coin]], placed there during [[minting]] so that it can be told if some of the metal from the edge is removed.  Removing metal from a coin was common practice during earlier times when coins made of precious metals circulated.

===Verb form===
'''milling'''

#Present participle of [[mill]], to cut or grind.
#:''The sawmill is working around the clock '''milling''' lumber for the new construction.''
#:''We are '''milling''' your grain now, the flour will be ready soon.''

